summary:
The Security Council,
 Reaffirming previous resolutions on Afghanistan, particularly resolution 1378 (2001),
 Reaffirming commitment to Afghanistan's sovereignty, independence, territorial integrity, and national unity,
 Stressing the Afghan people's right to determine their own political future,
 Determined to help end conflicts, promote national reconciliation, peace, stability, and human rights,
 Welcoming the Agreement on provisional arrangements in Afghanistan,
Noting the Agreement as a first step towards a broad-based, gender-sensitive, multi-ethnic, and representative government,
1. Endorses the Agreement on provisional arrangements;
2. Calls on Afghan groups to implement the Agreement, cooperating with the Interim Authority;
3. Reaffirms support to the Special Representative of the Secretary-General;
4. Will take further action to support Interim institutions and implementation of the Agreement;
5. Calls on Afghan groups to ensure humanitarian access and safety of humanitarian workers;
6. Calls on donors to assist with Afghanistan's rehabilitation, recovery, and reconstruction;
7. Decides to remain seized of the matter.
